 expired, Bruyere experiments with the interpretive affordances of allegory and fairytale, still life and travelogues. Each chapter places a vanitas motif—canvas, debris, toxics, paper, ark, meat, and light—in conversation with stories and images of the Anthropocene, from the Pleistocene Park geoengineering project to toxic legacies to in-vitro meat. Considering questions of quiet erasure and environmental memory, this book argues we ought to keep reading, even by the flickering light of extinction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEcocriticism2DLC. 0aEcocriticism. 0aHumanities2DLC. 0aHumanities. 0aVanitas (Art) 0aVanitas (Art)2DLC. 0aVanitas (Art). 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aAnthropocene.  aclose reading.  aearly modern.  aecocriticism.  aenvironmental memory.  aextinction.  ahumanistic inquiry.  astill life.  avanitas.  avisual culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z978311131826408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079132740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363679840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503636798423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503636798/original  a978-3-11-079132-7  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131826-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131918-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-13